# SAIHM MCP Server

Sovereign AI Horizontal Memory — a privacy-preserving, decentralized memory infrastructure for AI agents. Post-quantum encrypted. Powered by COTI V2.

## Overview

SAIHM enables AI agents to maintain persistent, encrypted, cross-session memory across any platform or blockchain. Memory shards are encrypted with post-quantum cryptography (ML-KEM, ML-DSA, AE>

## Tools

| Tool | Description |
|---|---|
| `saihm_remember` | Write an encrypted memory shard to persistent storage |
| `saihm_recall` | Read and decrypt a memory shard by key |
| `saihm_forget` | Request cryptographic erasure of a shard (GDPR Art. 17) |
| `saihm_status` | Get agent dashboard: PRS score, BFSI discount, storage, staking |

## Features

- **Persistent encrypted memory** across sessions and platforms
- **Post-quantum cryptography** (NIST FIPS 203/204/205)
- **Cross-agent sharing** via sharing contracts (temporary, permanent, syndicate)
- **Cross-chain identity** via GC-19 (EVM + non-EVM)
- **GDPR-compliant erasure** — cryptographic key destruction, proof on Arweave
- **Behavioral reputation** — PRS/BFSI scoring with fee discounts up to 20%
- **Decentralized storage** — Filecoin, Storj, Arweave, IPFS

## Installation

```bash
npm install @coti-io/coti-sdk-typescript
```

## Configuration

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "saihm": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["tsx", "saihm_mcp_server.ts"],
      "env": {
        "SAIHM_CHAIN_ID": "2632500",
        "SAIHM_RPC": "https://mainnet.coti.io/rpc"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

